# 🚧 Project Rules & Contribution Guidelines
## Fuel Queue Management System

These rules must be followed by all team members to ensure smooth development, avoid conflicts, and maintain code quality.

---

## 🌿 1. Branching Strategy

- NEVER push directly to `main` branch
- ALWAYS create a new branch for your work

### Branch Naming Convention:
- `feature/<feature-name>` → New features
- `bugfix/<bug-name>` → Bug fixes
- `hotfix/<urgent-fix>` → Critical fixes

### Example:
feature/login-system
bugfix/queue-display-error


---

## 🔀 2. Pull Requests & Merging

- DO NOT merge your own branch
- ALWAYS create a Pull Request (PR)
- At least one team member must review before merging

### Before creating PR:
- Test your code
- Make sure no errors
- Pull latest changes from `main`

---

## ⚠️ 3. Conflict Handling

- If GitHub shows conflicts → FIX them before merging
- NEVER ignore conflicts
- Ask team member if unsure

---

## 🧪 4. Testing Rules

Before pushing code:

- Check all pages are working
- Test login & register
- Test database operations
- Make sure no console errors

---

## 🗂️ 5. File Structure Rules

- Keep frontend and backend separate
- Do NOT create random files in root folder
- Follow project structure:
  /frontend
  /backend
  /database

---

## 🔐 6. Security Rules

- NEVER upload `.env` file
- NEVER expose database passwords
- Do NOT hardcode sensitive data

---

## 📸 7. Uploads & Files

- Do NOT upload large files to GitHub
- Ignore user-uploaded images (`uploads/` folder)

---

## 📝 8. Code Quality

- Write clean and readable code
- Use proper variable names
- Add comments when necessary

BAD:
```php
$a = 5;

GOOD:
 $queue_length = 5;
